did.head: Collection Summary

repository.corpname: Woodson Research Center, Rice University, Houston, Texas

did.unittitle: Rice University Office of Admissions records
did.abstract: Records reflecting the daily business of the Rice University Office of Admissions, including expense reports for faculty travel and for department spending, application records from potential faculty and graduate students, recruiting and documentation on incoming students.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The Office of Admission handles new student admission and new faculty. It also promotes the university with travel and recruitment events.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Records reflecting the daily business of the Rice University Office of Admissions, including expense reports for faculty travel and for department spending, application records from potential faculty and graduate students, recruiting planning and documentation of incoming students.

accessrestrict.head: Access Restrictions
accessrestrict.p: This material is restricted for privacy reasons. Permission to use this material must be obtained in writing from the Director of Admissions.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Stored off-site at the Library Service Center. Please request this material via woodson@rice.edu or call 713-348-2586.

acqinfo.head: Immediate Source of Acquisition
acqinfo.p: Transferred to the Woodson Research Center, 2007 and 2010.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Rice University Office of Admissions Records, 1979-2010, UA 142, Woodson Research Center, Fondren Library, Rice University.

userestrict.head: Conditions Governing Use
userestrict.p: Permission to publish material from the Office of Admission Records must be obtained from the Woodson Research Center, Fondren Library.
